Simplicity is good. Simplicity means low cost, low failure rate and longer life cycle.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Certainly nothing wrong with simplicity..but liquid fuel is hardly the most effective means of launch/propulsion.<br>
<br>
Case in point:  The STS antique.<br>
<br>
That huge main tank/booster is all liquid fuel..a construct larger than the craft it's designed to lift into orbit.  In addition to it's payload, it has to lift the mass of it's liquid-fuel contents into space, as well.<br>
<br>
It is simple, yes..and has the added benefit of a high level of controllability; in the event of a severe problem, the flow of fuel can be cut off and the burn can be terminated.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, the whole is attached to two, smaller, solid-fuel thrusters that are going to fire until their fuel is completely used up..no matter how early or late a problem might be detected.<br>
<br>
Having to use half, or more, of your total thrust just to launch the fuel container may be simpler..but it's not at all efficient.  And tying that to a booster that just cannot be turned off, once fired..even if a need to do so is almost immediately determined..threatens the actuality of the term &quot;low failure rate&quot;<br>
<br>
I know such has not been the direct case, where the STS is concerned, but does anyone have any figures for how many launch vehichles have blown up on the pad in the past few years..? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.whitetoweronline.com"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.whitetoweronline.com/hall/icons/barth-sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=q66stang>Q66stang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/20/03 10:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=319.topic&index=156>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Orion</span><hr size=1> John<br>
