<br>
About the time ORION was cancelled was about the time Silent Spring by Rachael Carson was published.  You had the incident where many sailors died due to fallout from a misdirected bomb test.  The Baby Tooth study finding concentrations of Sr-90 in teeth was big news.  There was a lot of political pressure against bomb testing at the time.  Sure it was ongoing, but it was extremely unpopular.  Many activists were actively trying to end bomb testing and all it would take is a new administration.<br>
<br>
NASA probably did not want to get caught up in a project they might not be able to continue.  With the future of bomb testing in question and with limited funding, NASA had to make a decision on one of its projects.  It chose Apollo, of course.  Had they chosen ORION and bomb testing been banned, NASA probably would have had to start all over.<br>
<br>
Considering the political envrionment at the time, I don't interpret it as &quot;won't work&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nuclaeon>Nuclaeon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 167<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/21/03 11:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=319.topic&index=163>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Orion</span><hr size=1> What I'm mainly saying is that the political reasons for cancelling ORION were believable.  If this were the early 50s and NASA made the same excuse, I would be more skeptical. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=q66stang>Q66stang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/23/03 10:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=319.topic&index=164>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Orion</span><hr size=1> Excellent article:<br>
